# Safe Refactor Rule

This codebase may contain legacy constraints, hidden contracts, and behavior-sensitive flows.

## Before refactoring

- inspect `docs/memory/systemPatterns.md`
- inspect `docs/memory/activeContext.md`
- inspect relevant docs under `docs/technical/` and `docs/product/` when needed
- identify whether the target area involves:
  - state transitions
  - event ordering
  - history/undo
  - cache invalidation
  - async initialization
  - browser timing behavior

## Required refactor standard

- preserve behavior unless the task explicitly changes it
- explain what invariants must remain true
- prefer small changes over broad rewrites
- verify assumptions before simplifying code paths

## If behavior changes intentionally

- add or update an ADR in `docs/decisions/`
- add a short link entry in `docs/memory/decisionLog.md`
- update affected memory/technical/product docs

## Do not

- Do not rewrite broad subsystems without explicit need.
- Do not replace nuanced flow with generic abstractions unless verified against real behavior.
- Do not remove legacy-looking logic just because it appears redundant.